template.transformer:
// Query results are available as the `data` variable
return data

update.query:
with
-- auxiliary table with one row per each day in our range
dates as (
  select 
    d::date AS day
  from generate_series(
    to_date({{DateRange.value.start }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD') - INTERVAL '30 DAYS',
    to_date({{DateRange.value.end }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD'),
    '1 day'
  ) as gs(d)

),
-- we select all the relevant events in our target range + 30 days before the start date
-- this is mostly to avoid having to query by dates and org sids in other subqueries
page_view_events as (
  select
    "userId" as user_id,
    date("createdAt") as day,
    'PAGE_VIEW' as event_type,
    count(1) as event_cnt
  from audit_trail_events
  where
    "actionType" = 'PAGE_VIEW'
    and date("createdAt") > (to_date({{ DateRange.value.start }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD') - INTERVAL '30 days') 
    and date("createdAt") <= to_date({{ DateRange.value.end }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD')
    and "organizationId" = ANY({{organizationIds.data}}) -- this is necessary to hit (organizationId, createdAt) index  
    and "userId" is not null  
  group by 1, 2, 3
),
page_save_events as (
  select
    "userId" as user_id,
    date("createdAt") as day,
    'PAGE_SAVE' as event_type,
    count(1) as event_cnt
  from page_saves
  where 
    date("createdAt") > (to_date({{ DateRange.value.start }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD') - INTERVAL '30 days') 
    and date("createdAt") <= to_date({{ DateRange.value.end }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD')
    and "userId" is not null  
  group by 1, 2, 3
),
workflow_save_events as (
  select
    "createdBy" as user_id,
    date("createdAt") as day,
    'WORKFLOW_SAVE' as event_type,
    count(1) as event_cnt
  from workflow_save
  where 
    date("createdAt") > (to_date({{ DateRange.value.end }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD') - INTERVAL '30 days') 
    and date("createdAt") <= to_date({{ DateRange.value.end }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD')
    and "createdBy" is not null  
  group by 1, 2, 3
),
all_events as (
  select 
    *
  from page_view_events
  union all
  select 
    *
  from page_save_events
  union all
  select
    *
  from workflow_save_events
),
-- get all distinct users we've seen in our date range
-- we're also adding 'none' user to make sure we get-non empty result even for org that had no user activity at all
all_users as (
  select 
    distinct user_id
  from all_events    
  union all
  select -1 as user_id
),
-- compute number of page saves and page views per user per day
user_activity_stats as (
  select
    day,
    user_id,
    sum(case when event_type IN ('PAGE_SAVE', 'WORKFLOW_SAVE') then event_cnt else 0 end) as save_cnt,
    sum(case when event_type = 'PAGE_VIEW' then event_cnt else 0 end) as page_view_cnt
  from all_events
  group by day, user_id
),
-- that's just all possible combinations of dates and users that we care about
user_day_pairs as (
  select
    day,
    user_id
  from dates cross join all_users  
),
-- user_activity_stats will only contain rows for days when user had _some_ activity
-- now we're adding rows for all missing days, so that we can run our 30 day window aggregations for every day
activity_by_user_day as (
  select
    ud_pairs.day as day,
    ud_pairs.user_id as user_id,
    coalesce(activity.save_cnt, 0) as save_cnt,
    coalesce(activity.page_view_cnt, 0) as page_view_cnt
  from user_day_pairs as ud_pairs
  left join user_activity_stats as activity
  on ud_pairs.day = activity.day and ud_pairs.user_id = activity.user_id
),
-- compute total page views and saves in 30d trailing window for every user and every day
cumulative_30d_activity_by_user_day as (
  select 
    day,
    user_id,
    sum(save_cnt) over (partition by user_id order by day rows 29 preceding) as save_cnt,
    sum(page_view_cnt) over (partition by user_id order by day rows 29 preceding) as page_view_cnt
  from activity_by_user_day      
),
-- now we have everything to determine the type of each user for every date in our range
user_type_by_day as (
  select 
    day,
    user_id,
    case 
      when save_cnt >= 5 then 'builder'
      when save_cnt < 5 and page_view_cnt > 0 then 'enduser'
      else 'none'
    end as user_type
  from cumulative_30d_activity_by_user_day
  where day >= to_date({{ DateRange.value.start }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD') AND day <= to_date({{ DateRange.value.end }}, 'YYYY-MM-DD')      
)
select
  day,
  sum(case when user_type = 'builder' then 1 else 0 end) as "builders",
  sum(case when user_type = 'enduser' then 1 else 0 end) as "endUsers"
from user_type_by_day
group by day
order by day
